{
"query": "from(bucket: "Jetson")
  |> range(start: 1h)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == v.measurments)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "jetson_Temp AO" or r["_field"] == "jetson_Temp CPU" or r["_field"] == "jetson_Temp GPU" or r["_field"] == "jetson_Temp PLL" or r["_field"] == "jetson_Temp thermal")
  |> aggregateWindow(every: v.windowPeriod, fn: last, createEmpty: false)
  |> yield(name: "last")"
}

{
"description": "updated my task",
"every": "10m",
"flux": "option task = {name: "mytask", every: 10m, offset: 1m}
 from(bucket: "system")
 |> range(start: -task.every)
 |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "cpu")
 |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "usage_user")
 |> filter(fn: (r) => r["cpu"] == "cpu-total")
 |> aggregateWindow(every: 5m, fn: mean, createEmpty: false)
 |> to(bucket: "test")
",

}

item.name: Retrieve all logs for a task

body.raw:
{
"orgID": "{{orgID}}",
"status": "active",
"flux": "option task = {name: "mytask", every: 10m, offset: 1m}
 from(bucket: "system")
 |> range(start: -task.every)
 |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "cpu")
 |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "usage_user")
 |> filter(fn: (r) => r["cpu"] == "cpu-total")
 |> aggregateWindow(every: 5m, fn: mean, createEmpty: false)
 |> to(bucket: "test")
",
"description": "downsamples total cpu usage_user data into 5m averages every 10m"
}
